,"meanings":["English (of Norman origin):","nickname from Old French <i>percehaie</i> ‘pierce hedge’ (Old French <i>percer</i> ‘to pierce, penetrate’ + <i>haie</i> ‘hedge, fence’), perhaps with the sense of someone breaking into an enclosure. <i>Percehaie</i> is the name of one of the sons of the foxes Renart and Hermeline in the medieval French epic <i>Roman de Renart</i>, whose earliest known version is from the 1170s. The surname is older than that, but it may originate in a nickname for the fox as ‘enclosure piercer’, perhaps amounting to ‘chicken thief’.","habitational name from any of several places called Percy in Calvados, Eure, and Manche; William <i>de Perci</i>, the Domesday tenant-in-chief and under-tenant of Hugh, Earl of Chester, came from either Percy-en-Auge (Eure) or Percy (Manche)."],"variants":[{"name":"Piercey","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Piercy","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Pearcey","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Peercy","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Pearcy","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]}]},{"name":"Blanche","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname for a blonde, from <i>blanche</i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Blanche DE PERCY was born in 1070, in Percy, Manche, Lower Normandy, France, her father, Mainfred DE PERCY, was 30 and her mother, Margaret, was 20. She had at least 1 son with Geoffroy DE MONTFELIX. She died in Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France."},"et":{"1070–":"1070–Surnud","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1070–Male":"1070–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France":"Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France":"Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1070–":"1070–Kuollut","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1070–Male":"1070–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France":"Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Ranska","Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France":"Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, Ranska"},"fr":{"1070–":"1070–Décédée","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","1070–Male":"1070–Décédé","1090–Male":"1090–Décédé","1040–Male":"1040–Décédé","1050–Female":"1050–Décédée","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France":"Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France","Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Chavot-Courcourt, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France","Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France":"Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Blanche DE PERCY est née en 1070, à Percy, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France, son père, Mainfred DE PERCY, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Margaret, avait 20 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Geoffroy DE MONTFELIX. Elle est décédée à Saint-Jean-Saint-Germain, Indre-et-Loire, Cen